{"session_id": 48, "bill_id": 14277, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1035, "bill_title": "permit the State of South Dakota to waive performance and payment bonds for public improvements under certain circumstances.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Performance Bonds", "Public Improvements", "State Government"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 14277, "bill_version_id": 80698, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1999-01-09T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to permit the State of South Dakota to waive performance and payment bonds for public improvements under certain circumstances. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 5-21 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The State of South Dakota, acting through the Bureau of Administration, may waive the requirement of a performance and payment bond on state projects if the awarded contract does not exceed one hundred thousand dollars. 750 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.016 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 14277, "bill_version_id": 80699, "bill_version": "Senate State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "1999-01-30T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to permit the State of South Dakota to waive performance and payment bonds for public improvements under certain circumstances. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 5-21 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The State of South Dakota, acting through the Bureau of Administration, shall waive the requirement of a performance and payment bond, before the bid letting, on state projects if the awarded contract does not exceed fifty thousand dollars. BILL HISTORY 1/1